						<summary>

						<p>Back side of the Kṛishṇa image in the Kaṇigalaṅka in the Kṛishṇa river.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Fasli year 1249</hi> which roughly corresponds to 1799-80 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the demarcation between Kaṇigalaṅka, the hamlet of Ayiḷūru and Annavaramlaṅka, the hamlet of Annavaram.</p>						

						</summary>
